Living in the West Valley, options for locally owned bakeries are slim pickings. However, this would be worth the drive if I didn't live near by. The bear claws are freshly baked with a rich almond paste center and always on point. Also, there are some almond bar treats (I'm not sure what the proper name is) that are our go to pastry. I have also had the fruit danish and some of the cookie selections, never disappointed here!

